Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "krava" in different forms and positions:

1. *Krava* pasla travu na livadi. (The *cow* grazed on the grass in the meadow.)
2. Ova *krava* je velika i crna. (This *cow* is big and black.)
3. Čuo sam da je neko ukrao *krave* iz tora. (I heard that someone stole *cows* from the barn.)
4. Kada bih imao farmu, uzgajao bih *krave*. (If I had a farm, I would raise *cows*.)
5. *Kravi* je teško kretati se po blatnjavoj stazi. (It's hard for a *cow* to move on a muddy path.)
6. Moramo nahraniti sve *krave* prije nego što padne mrak. (We need to feed all the *cows* before it gets dark.)
7. Mama je kupila svježi sir od *kravljeg* mlijeka. (Mom bought fresh cheese made from *cow's* milk.)
8. Nismo mogli doći do *kravljeg* sira jer je bilo rasprodano. (We couldn't get the *cow's* cheese because it was sold out.)
9. Dječak se igrao u blizini *kravljeg* tora. (The boy was playing near the *cow's* barn.)
10. *Kravama* treba dovoljno prostora za kretanje. (Cows need enough space to move around.)

I hope this helps!